  "title": "Management Consultant Associate",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Build and maintain relationships with Ultra High Net Worth (UHNW) individuals and their businesses.</li>\n  <li>Provide bespoke investment advice and manage discretionary portfolios.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with private banks to optimize client solutions.</li>\n  <li>Establish and advise on Single Family Offices (SFOs) and Multi Family Offices (MFOs).</li>\n  <li>Offer strategic planning for generational wealth transfer.</li>\n  <li>Deliver high-net-worth insurance solutions tailored to client needs.</li>\n  <li>Assist with trust structures, buy-sell agreements, and tax optimization strategies.</li>\n  <li> Implement asset ringfencing and risk mitigation strategies</li>\n  <li>Any other ad-hoc assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p>\n<p>• Strong analytical and problem-solving skills</p>\n<p>• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</p>\n<p>• Attention to detail and a high level of accuracy</p>\n<p>• Ability to work independently and as a team</p>\n<p>• Experience in Management Consultancy, Banking, Finance, Asset Management, Trust, Insurance industry is preferred</p>\n<p>• Bachelor's degree in Finance, Business, Economics, Mathematics or a related field are preferred</p>",
